# Ix Memory System

This project uses Ix Memory for persistent, time-aware context.

## Project
- Name: {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Interface
Use the `ix` CLI exclusively. Do NOT use MCP tools — the CLI is the canonical agent interface.
All commands support `--format json` for machine-readable output.

## MANDATORY RULES
1. BEFORE answering codebase questions → use targeted `ix` CLI commands (see routing below)
2. AFTER making any design/architecture decision → run `ix decide`
3. When noticing contradictory information → run `ix conflicts`
4. NEVER guess about codebase facts when Ix has structured data
5. After modifying code → run `ix ingest` on changed files
6. When the user states a goal → run `ix truth add`

## Ix CLI Command Routing
- `ix search` — find entities by name/kind/language
- `ix explain` — understand a symbol (structure, container, calls)
- `ix read` — read source code by path or symbol
- `ix entity` — full entity details by ID
- `ix text` — fast lexical search (ripgrep)
- `ix callers` / `ix callees` — call graph navigation
- `ix contains` — members of a class/module
- `ix imports` / `ix imported-by` — import graph
- `ix depends` — dependency impact analysis
- `ix decisions` — list past design decisions
- `ix history` / `ix diff` — temporal queries

## Do NOT Use
- `ix query` — deprecated, oversized low-signal responses
- MCP tools — deprecated, use CLI instead
